===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, equivalent to {{term|yond|lang=en}} (from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|geond|ġeond|lang=ang}}) + {{term|-er|lang=en}}, as in {{term|hither|lang=en}}, {{term|thither|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|ginder||lang=nl}} ('over there').

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# In a distant, [[indicate]]d place; over [[there]].
#: ''Whose home is that '''yonder'''?''

